From: Xiubo Li <xiubli@redhat.com>
Date: Wed, 9 Nov 2022 11:00:39 +0800
Subject: ceph: avoid putting the realm twice when decoding snaps fails
Git-commit: 51884d153f7ec85e18d607b2467820a90e0f4359
Patch-mainline: v6.1-rc6
References: bsc#1206051

When decoding the snaps fails it maybe leaving the 'first_realm'
and 'realm' pointing to the same snaprealm memory. And then it'll
put it twice and could cause random use-after-free, BUG_ON, etc
issues.

Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Link: https://tracker.ceph.com/issues/57686
Signed-off-by: Xiubo Li <xiubli@redhat.com>
Reviewed-by: Ilya Dryomov <idryomov@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Ilya Dryomov <idryomov@gmail.com>
Acked-by: Luis Henriques <lhenriques@suse.com>

---
 fs/ceph/snap.c |    3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/fs/ceph/snap.c
+++ b/fs/ceph/snap.c
@@ -705,7 +705,7 @@ int ceph_update_snap_trace(struct ceph_m
 	struct ceph_mds_snap_realm *ri;    /* encoded */
 	__le64 *snaps;                     /* encoded */
 	__le64 *prior_parent_snaps;        /* encoded */
-	struct ceph_snap_realm *realm = NULL;
+	struct ceph_snap_realm *realm;
 	struct ceph_snap_realm *first_realm = NULL;
 	struct ceph_snap_realm *realm_to_rebuild = NULL;
 	int rebuild_snapcs;
@@ -716,6 +716,7 @@ int ceph_update_snap_trace(struct ceph_m
 
 	dout("update_snap_trace deletion=%d\n", deletion);
 more:
+	realm = NULL;
 	rebuild_snapcs = 0;
 	ceph_decode_need(&p, e, sizeof(*ri), bad);
 	ri = p;

